\begin_layout Itemize
Process performance dashboards.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And we can analyze bottlenecks, workloads and rework.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Bottleneck analysis in the activity perspective
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\emph on
resource-capacity bottleneck 
\emph default
can be detected when we see an activity in a process map whose incoming
 arcs are all slow.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\emph on
slow handoff
\emph default
 between activities can be detected when we see two consecutive activies
 whose connecting arc is very slow.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An 
\emph on
activity bottleneck
\emph default
 can be detected when we see an activity that is slow.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Bottleneck analysis in the resource perspective
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If we see a process map from the point of view of the resources used, we
 can detect a 
\emph on
resource bottleneck
\emph default
 when a resource is very slow and 
\emph on
slow handoffs
\emph default
 between specific resources when the connecting arc between two resources
 is slow.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Workload analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can define:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Potentially overused resources
\series default
 as those with high total frequency and/or high total duration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Potentially undersued resources
\series default
 are those with low total frequency and/or low total duration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Rework analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Rework is the repetition of activities within the same case.
 It can happen in several forms:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Self loop
\series default
: an activity is repeated 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 times in a row.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Short loop
\series default
: two activities are repeated one after the other.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Indirect repetition (loop)
\series default
: several activities are executed several times in sequence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To analyze repetitions, one can try to answer:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What type of repetition is present?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
How often is an activity / series of activities repeated?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
How many cases showcase this repetition? How often does it occur?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Which cases are affected? How do they differ from cases where there is no
 repetition?
\end_layout

